{"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"running the idle function).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call doesn’t block too long","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and miss the next timeout."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"since i